Phase 1 — Logging policy, categories, and interface contract (`@backend-dev` + `@business-analyst`)
- [ ] Define shared logging policy for all backend services.
- [ ] Define category names for endpoint, hibernate transaction, entity, session, SQL, and filter logs.
- [ ] Document default log level behavior and escalation to DEBUG/TRACE.
- [ ] Define logging service interface contract for emitting classes (emit + collected events retrieval).
- [ ] Define how emitted logs are collected using system-wide logging level threshold.
- [ ] Define file-routing policy: separate log files by Hibernate subtype and by new logging category/type.

Phase 2 — DAO proof of concept (`@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Verify that `mbook-quarkus` DAO is called via `@Inject` (CDI proxy) — interceptor prerequisite.
- [ ] Verify callers of `mbooks-quarkus` `DAO.instance()` in controllers and switch to `@Inject DAO dao` where needed to enable CDI interception.
- [ ] Add `@ObservedLog` annotations to DAO methods in `mbook-quarkus` (annotation-only; no method body changes).
- [ ] Add `@ObservedLog` annotations to DAO methods in `mbooks-quarkus` (annotation-only; no method body changes).
- [ ] Confirm interceptor builds `source` as `ClassName.methodName` from `InvocationContext`.
- [ ] Confirm interceptor captures parameters only when `includeArgs = true` and that sensitive params are redacted.
- [ ] Validate that collected logs include only events enabled by current system log level.
- [ ] Document DAO PoC findings and rollout recommendations for non-DAO services.

Phase 3 — Existing logging migration and formatting (`@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Inventory current service logs and current Hibernate log emitters/handlers.
- [ ] Reformat existing logs to agreed structured format without removing current coverage.
- [ ] Reformat existing Hibernate logs to agreed structured format while preserving category identity.
- [ ] Confirm backward-compatible log field naming for dashboards/queries where required.

Phase 4 — Service logging rollout (`@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Add endpoint call logs to all backend services.
- [ ] Add Hibernate transaction summary logs.
- [ ] Add entity operation logs where meaningful.
- [ ] Add servlet/JAX-RS filter logs for auth/cookie/request processing.
- [ ] Add session state logs in services managing login/session flows.
- [ ] Route newly added categories to dedicated log files per category/type policy.

Phase 5 — SQL and Hibernate detail levels (`@backend-dev` + `@performance-engineer`)
- [ ] Implement short SQL info logging.
- [ ] Implement longer SQL debug logging.
- [ ] Implement SQL/transaction error logging.
- [ ] Keep Hibernate log types split into separate files (transaction, SQL, statistics, and other configured types).
- [ ] Review Hibernate and SQL logging overhead under normal load.

Phase 6 — Security review (`@security-specialist` + `@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Identify sensitive fields/headers/cookies to redact or suppress.
- [ ] Validate auth/session logs do not leak secrets or token material.
- [ ] Validate payment-related logs do not expose nonces or credential-like values.

Phase 7 — Grafana log visualization (`@devops` + `@backend-dev`)
- [ ] Add log ingestion backend for Grafana queries (expected: Loki or equivalent).
- [ ] Route backend service logs into Grafana-queryable datasource.
- [ ] Add dashboard panels or Explore views for service, level, and category.
- [ ] Add panels/queries for endpoint failures, filter rejections, slow SQL, and session events.
- [ ] Verify file-split log streams remain queryable by category without cross-mixing.

Phase 8 — Verification (`@testing-engineer` + `@performance-engineer`)
- [ ] Verify each service emits expected structured logs for representative flows.
- [ ] Verify Grafana can query/filter logs by service, level, and category.
- [ ] Verify DAO PoC interface contract behavior across INFO/DEBUG/TRACE level switches.
- [ ] Verify separate files are used for Hibernate types and new category logs.
- [ ] Verify default logging volume is acceptable.
- [ ] Capture baseline performance impact of new logging configuration.

Phase 9 — Documentation (`@backend-dev` + `@devops`)
- [ ] Update per-module READMEs with logging categories and level controls.
- [ ] Document interface contract usage guidelines for classes that must emit logs.
- [ ] Document log file routing map (existing + Hibernate + new categories).
- [ ] Update observability docs with Grafana log-visualization setup.
- [ ] Document how to temporarily enable DEBUG/TRACE for investigations.
